  "texts": [
    "However, with further research, it has been found that these methods generate fixed-length embeddings when dealing with graphs of different sizes, which limits their expressive power to some extent.",
    "To overcome this limitation, some studies have begun to explore the use of attention mechanisms to enhance pooling operations (Li et al. 2015; Tran et al. 2018; Itoh et al. 2022).",
    "Although the self-attention mechanisms can improve the performance of pooling operations, fixed-length embeddings remain a challenge.",
    "Set2Set (Vinyals et al. 2015) achieves dynamic adaptation to the size of the input graph by introducing a memory bank that changes with the size of the input graph and using two LSTMs (Hochreiter and Schmidhuber 1997) (one reader and one writer) to iteratively update the global representation.",
    "This pooling method solves the problem of fixed-length embedding and improves the flexibility of pooling operations."
  ],
